Seventh Avenue South, west side, south of Morton Street.
March 29th, 1933.
P.L. Sperr,Photographers.
The New York Times of March 12, 1940 reports the lease of site known as 62-4 Leroy Street and 16-18 Seventh Avenue South to a firm of builders to be improved with a 6 story apartment house for Fall occupancy. This plot has frontages of 50.4 feet on the former and 77.4 on the latter. A partial view of same appears here. It is the triangular corner (S.W.) distinguished by the tenement with the sign "I Will Share". The structure bearing this legend is to be included in conjunction with the Sinclair gas station
